 General:
 --------
   o The Adaptec RAID Monitoring Plugin is a Nagios/Icinga plugin to check
     the Adaptec RAID Controller for warnings or critical errors.
   o It is written in Perl and uses the Arcconf Command Line Utility to interact
     with the RAID Controller.

 Current Version:
 ----------------
   o The current version of the check_adaptec_raid plugin is available at the
     Thomas Krenn git-server:
   o http://git.thomas-krenn.com/check_adaptec_raid.git

 Functionalities:
 ----------------
   o Checks the Controller Status,
   o Physical Device Status,
   o Logical Device Status and
   o ZMM Status

 Requirements:
 -------------
   o On the system to be monitored:
     + check_adaptec_raid plugin
     + arcconf
     + sudoers entry for user nagios and arcconf:
       (example: nagios ALL=(root) NOPASSWD:/sbin/arcconf)
     + NRPE (optional): command definition
   o On the Icinga-server:
     + command definition
     + service definition

 Parameter usage (example):
 --------------------------
   o ./check_adaptec_raid -T 30,40 -C 1 -LD 0,1 -PD 1 -z 0
   o AACRAID CRITICAL (Ctrl #1): [Ctrl. Status critical, Ctrl. temp. critical,
     Log. device failed/degraded]
